Subject: [PATCH 0004] ia64/sn2: tiocx.c — const device_driver in bus match callback

The bus_type .match callback signature was constified in 6.16:
  int (*match)(struct device *dev, const struct device_driver *drv)

Update tiocx_match() to take const struct device_driver *, and
propagate const to the local cx_drv pointer since it's derived
from the now-const driver via container_of.

No other SN2 driver files define bus_type .match callbacks.

---
 arch/ia64/sn/kernel/tiocx.c | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

--- a/arch/ia64/sn/kernel/tiocx.c	2026-03-14 16:34:26.000000000 +0000
+++ b/arch/ia64/sn/kernel/tiocx.c	2026-03-14 17:30:46.100985422 +0000
@@ -48,10 +48,10 @@
  *
  * Returns 1 if match, 0 otherwise.
  */
-static int tiocx_match(struct device *dev, struct device_driver *drv)
+static int tiocx_match(struct device *dev, const struct device_driver *drv)
 {
 	struct cx_dev *cx_dev = to_cx_dev(dev);
-	struct cx_drv *cx_drv = to_cx_driver(drv);
+	const struct cx_drv *cx_drv = to_cx_driver(drv);
 	const struct cx_device_id *ids = cx_drv->id_table;
 
 	if (!ids)
